============================================================
MANUSCRIPT-READY RESULTS TEXT
============================================================

A total of 569 patients (357 benign, 212 malignant) were included.
Baseline characteristics are summarized in Table 1.

The Logistic Regression achieved an AUC of 0.995 (0.990-1.000), sensitivity of 0.943 (0.904-0.967), specificity of 0.992 (0.976-0.997), and accuracy of 0.974 (0.957-0.984).
The Random Forest achieved an AUC of 0.987 (0.976-0.998), sensitivity of 0.934 (0.892-0.960), specificity of 0.966 (0.942-0.981), and accuracy of 0.954 (0.934-0.969).
The SVM (RBF) achieved an AUC of 0.994 (0.989-0.999), sensitivity of 0.958 (0.921-0.978), specificity of 0.989 (0.972-0.996), and accuracy of 0.977 (0.961-0.987).

ROC curves for all three models are shown in Figure 1.
